import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['precipitation'] = pd.to_numeric(data['precipitation'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['precipitation'])]
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='precipitation', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['precipitation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(x=data['precipitation'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation?')
    plt.xlabel('Precipitation (inches)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_max', data=data, color='blue')
    plt.title('How does the maximum temperature vary over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Maximum Temperature (F)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='wind', y='temp_max', data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.axhline(y=data['temp_max'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Temperature')
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind speed and temperature?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data['count'] = 1
    data = data.groupby('weather').sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values('count', ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="weather", y="count", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set(xlabel='Weather Condition', ylabel='Count')
    plt.title('What is the most common weather condition observed in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
